    <article class="blog-post">
      <h1>How to Choose Between a Treadmill and an Elliptical</h1>
      <p>If you're setting up a home gym, you might wonder: Should I buy a treadmill or an elliptical? Both offer great cardio, but here are key differences:</p>

      <h2>1. Impact on Joints</h2>
      <p>Ellipticals are lower-impact, making them ideal for users with knee or hip concerns.</p>

      <h2>2. Calorie Burn</h2>
      <p>Treadmills typically burn more calories per hour, especially when used at higher inclines or speeds.</p>

      <h2>3. Muscle Engagement</h2>
      <p>Ellipticals engage upper and lower body muscles simultaneously, while treadmills focus more on legs and core.</p>

      <p>Still undecided? <a href="get-quote.html" class="btn">Get a Quote</a> — we service both types of equipment across the GTA.</p>
    </article>

