      <h1>5 Signs Your Gym Equipment Needs a Repair</h1>
      <p>Prevent costly breakdowns with early detection. Here are five warning signs:</p>

      <ul>
        <li>✅ Strange noises or grinding sounds</li>
        <li>✅ Inconsistent speeds or resistance levels</li>
        <li>✅ Unresponsive touch panels or consoles</li>
        <li>✅ Burning smells or overheating</li>
        <li>✅ Visible damage or loose parts</li>
      </ul>

      <p>If you notice any of these, don’t delay. <a href="get-quote.html" class="btn">Request Service Now</a>.</p>
    </article>

    <!-- Blog Post 3 -->
    <article class="blog-post">
      <h1>NordicTrack, Sole, Horizon & Precor Treadmill Error Codes</h1>
      <p>Treadmills can display a range of error codes. Here are the most common ones we fix:</p>

      <h2><a href="nordictrack-repair.html">NordicTrack</a></h2>
      <p><strong>LS1 / LS2:</strong> Speed sensor issue — clean or replace the sensor.</p>

      <h2><a href="sole-repair.html">Sole</a></h2>
      <p><strong>E7:</strong> Motor error — check wiring and consult a technician.</p>

      <h2><a href="horizon-repair.html">Horizon</a></h2>
      <p><strong>H1:</strong> Incline calibration failed — recalibrate or service incline motor.</p>

      <h2><a href="precor-repair.html">Precor</a></h2>
      <p><strong>31:</strong> Drive motor failure — often needs a technician’s visit.</p>

      <h2><a href="lifefitness-repair.html">Life Fitness</a></h2>
      <p><strong>E1:</strong> Communication error — inspect cables and contact service.</p>

